## review-merge-gate.bot — guided review-&-merge gate demo.
##
## An agent implements a small change in a per-run worktree, then a review
## gate (interaction: review) walks the operator through testing it via a
## companion-driven dialogue and squash-merges the worktree once approved.
## Optionally provisions a review environment (driven by a custom prompt)
## the operator can open in the studio Browser pane to actually test.
##
##   iterion run examples/review-merge-gate.bot \
##     --var feature_prompt="Add a CHANGELOG entry for the new feature" \
##     --var review_env_prompt="Start the dev server: npm run dev (port 5173)"
##
## Exits: approve → squash-merge; force-merge (studio) → merge without a
## verdict; request changes → loop back to the implementer.

vars:
  feature_prompt: string = "Add a one-line CHANGELOG entry describing a notable recent change."
  review_env_prompt: string = ""   ## optional: how to make the change testable (serve/deploy/build)

schema impl_result:
  summary: string

schema review_verdict:
  decision: string      ## approved | changes_requested
  confidence: string    ## low | medium | high
  blockers: string[]

schema provision_result:
  url: string
  notes: string

prompt provision_system:
  You provision a review environment so a human can test the change.
  Follow these operator instructions exactly:

  {{vars.review_env_prompt}}

  If the instructions are empty, do nothing and return an empty url.
  When you start a server or deploy, report the URL the human should open
  in `url`. Never block the run — start long-running servers in the
  background (e.g. `nohup … &`) and return immediately.

prompt impl_system:
  You are an implementer. Make the smallest correct change for the task,
  run the repo's own tests if they are quick, then commit your work with a
  clear message. The worktree IS your workspace — you MUST commit (the
  review gate squash-merges your commits once the human approves).

prompt impl_user:
  Task to implement:

  {{vars.feature_prompt}}

prompt companion_system:
  You are a review companion. A human is about to test a code change.
  From the diff you are shown, write PRECISE, numbered steps for how to
  test it — exact commands to run and what to look for. Read each reply
  and react: if they report success, set decision=approved with your
  confidence (low|medium|high); if they hit problems, set
  decision=changes_requested and list concrete blockers. Set
  needs_human_input=false only once you have a confident verdict. Keep
  every message short and concrete.

agent provision_review_env:
  backend: "claude_code"
  system: provision_system
  output: provision_result

agent implement:
  backend: "claude_code"
  system: impl_system
  user: impl_user
  output: impl_result

human ship_review:
  interaction: review
  model: "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6"
  system: companion_system
  output: review_verdict
  review_url: "{{outputs.provision_review_env.url}}"
  posture: human_required
  merge_strategy: squash
  merge_into: current
  max_turns: 8

workflow review_merge_gate:
  entry: provision_review_env
  worktree: auto
  provision_review_env -> implement
  implement -> ship_review
  ship_review -> done when "decision == 'approved'"
  ship_review -> implement when "decision == 'changes_requested'" as fix_loop(5)
  ship_review -> fail
